---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Blog — Fernando Delgado" bodyClass="collection-type-blog blog-layout-center">

  <div class="article-list hfeed">

    <!-- Post 1 -->
    <article class="hentry promoted promoted-block-image category-interviews tag-interviews tag-tips article-index-1">
      <header>
        <h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">
          <a href="/blog/how-to-prepare-for-product-management-interviews">How to prepare for Product Management interviews?</a>
        </h1>
        <div class="meta article-meta">
          <span class="date"><time datetime="2016-04-25">April 25, 2016</time></span>
          <span class="author">Fernando Delgado</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="special-content">
        <figure class="sqs-block-image-figure intrinsic">
          <div class="image-block-wrapper">
            <div style="height:380px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:8px;">
              <img
                src="/images/blog-interview-prep.jpg"
                alt="Photo courtesy of tookapic"
                loading="lazy"
                style="display:block;object-fit:cover;width:100%;height:100%;object-position:50% 50%;"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <div class="image-caption"><p>Photo courtesy of tookapic - <a href="https://stock.tookapic.com/photos/23993" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://stock.tookapic.com/photos/23993</a></p></div>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="body entry-content">
        <p>Typical Product Manager interviews will consist of questions in the following areas:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Behavioral</li>
          <li>Technical</li>
          <li>Analytical</li>
          <li>Product sense</li>
          <li>Strategy/vision (for somewhat senior candidates)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Some companies will explicitly judge your performance in areas like creativity, leadership, and cultural fit, but even then, the types of questions they ask to assess this will fall into one of the above categories. I will share the types of questions in each group and how to prepare for them.</p>
        <a class="read-more" href="/blog/how-to-prepare-for-product-management-interviews">Read more</a>
      </div>

    </article>

    <!-- Post 2 -->
    <article class="hentry promoted promoted-block-image category-career tag-apm tag-career tag-internships article-index-2">
      <header>
        <h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">
          <a href="/blog/how-to-become-a-product-manager">How to become a Product Manager (for college students)</a>
        </h1>
        <div class="meta article-meta">
          <span class="date"><time datetime="2016-04-13">April 13, 2016</time></span>
          <span class="author">Fernando Delgado</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="special-content">
        <figure class="sqs-block-image-figure intrinsic">
          <div class="image-block-wrapper">
            <div style="height:380px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:8px;">
              <img
                src="/images/blog-career-path.jpg"
                alt=""
                loading="lazy"
                style="display:block;object-fit:cover;width:100%;height:100%;object-position:50% 50%;"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="body entry-content">
        <p>I recently got the following question from a college student on Facebook's HH Product Management group: "What kind of path would I have to take (for university and beyond) to be prepared for a Product Manager role?"</p>
        <p>Here are the concrete steps I would highly recommend anyone who is still in college...</p>
        <a class="read-more" href="/blog/how-to-become-a-product-manager">Read more</a>
      </div>

    </article>

    <!-- Post 3 -->
    <article class="hentry promoted promoted-block-image category-interviews tag-communication tag-hiring tag-interviews article-index-3">
      <header>
        <h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">
          <a href="/blog/factors-that-impact-your-interview-scores">Factors that impact your interview scores</a>
        </h1>
        <div class="meta article-meta">
          <span class="date"><time datetime="2016-04-07">April 7, 2016</time></span>
          <span class="author">Fernando Delgado</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="special-content">
        <figure class="sqs-block-image-figure intrinsic">
          <div class="image-block-wrapper">
            <div style="height:380px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:8px;">
              <img
                src="/images/blog-interview-scores.jpg"
                alt=""
                loading="lazy"
                style="display:block;object-fit:cover;width:100%;height:100%;object-position:50% 50%;border-radius:8px;"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="body entry-content">
        <p>Some people believe that an interview is simply about getting the "right" answers. In reality, the company conducting the interview is looking at many additional factors. I'll go over them below.</p>
        <a class="read-more" href="/blog/factors-that-impact-your-interview-scores">Read more</a>
      </div>

    </article>

  </div>

</Layout>
